article.headline: Columbia 69, Navy 63
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Matt Preston scored 23 points as Columbia downed Navy, 69-63 Monday night. Preston had 17 points in the first half as the Lions built a 29-24 lead. Mack Montgomery added a career-high 15 points for the Lions, all in the second half. With the win, Columbia (10-4) matched its victory total from last season when it finished 10-17. Navy (4-12) lost its sixth straight game and suffered the 10th loss in its last 11 games. Matt Fannin led the Midshipmen with 16 points and Greg Sprink added 13 points and a game-high nine rebounds. Navy outrebounded the Lions, 48-37, but committed 22 turnovers and shot just 37.5 percent from the floor, making just 5 of 25 three-pointers. Columbia made 21 of 29 free throws. From the floor, the Lions made half their shots in the second half after shooting just 28.1 percent in the first half. Navy led 24-21 before Columbia outscored the Mids 8-0 to close the first half. The Mids trailed by 44-41 with 11:30 to play, but Columbia pulled ahead by 62-51 with 3:29 to play. Navy closed to within 67-63 with 13 seconds to play before Preston made two free throws to ice the win.
